What is AngularJS.

    - AngularJS is Client Side JavaScript Framework.

    - AngularJS Follows the MVC Design Pattern.

        M - Model   (JavaScript Variables)

        V - View    (HTML / HTML5)

        C - Controller (JavaScript Functions)


        Ex.

            Var s = "Angular2";

            function my_fun(){

                document.getElementById("my_paragraph").innerHTML = s;
            }

            <p id="my_paragraph"></p>

    - AngularJS have a so many predefined Modules , As a Angular Developer we can use the Predefined
      Modules.


      1.ngAnimate
            - used to develop the Animations in Angular Applications.


      2.ngMessages
            - used to develop the Client Side Form Validations.


      3.ngStorage.
            - used to develop the Storages Related Applications in AngularJS.

            - we have two types of Storages

                    1.localStorage
                    2.sessionStorage

      4.ngRoute

            - used to develop the Single Page Applications.

            - ngRoute Module is the Native Module.

            - No Body using the ngRoute Module now a days becuase of it's limitations.


      5.ui.router

            - used to develop the Single Page Applications.

            - it is a 3rd party Module.

            - Now a days all  all the Projects Using ui.router Module in Single Page Application Development.


    Ex.

            - Please Develop the Angular Application with Following Features

                1.SPA - ui.router

                2.Storages

                3.Client Side Validations.

                4.Animations


            index.html
            -
            <!DOCTYPE html>
            <html ng-app="app">

                    //Logic Goes Here

                <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.6.0/angular.min.js"></script>
                <script>
                   angular.module("app" , ["ui.router","ngStorage","ngMessages","ngAnimate"]);
                </script>
            </html>


Advantages Of AngularJS.


1.We Can Directly work with the HTML DOM.
    DOM - Document Object Model.


Ex.

    Copy the Data From One Div to Another Div by using HTML & JavaScript.


    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html>
        <div id="div_one">Hello</div>
        <div id="div_two"></div>
        <button onClick="copy()">Copy</button>
        <script>
            function copy(){
                document.getElementById("div_one").innerHTML =
                document.getElementBuid("div_two").value;
            }
        </script>
    </html>




    Copy the Data from One Div to Another Div By using AngularJS.

    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html ng-app="app">
        <div ng-model="div_one">Hello</div>
        <h1 ng-bind="div_one"></h1>
        <script src=".../angular.min.js"></script>
    </html>


    - Framework starts the execution from ng-app directive.

    - ng-model stores the application data in a object.

    - ng-bind "binds" the model data to the HTML Elements.


    [Note. we can work with the HTML DOM without javascript ].